{"cursor":"9856","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Ricardo Costa image = alt = caption = birth_name = Ricardo Costa\n| birth_date = birth_place = Peniche, Portugal death_date = death_place =\n| nationality = other_names = known_for = occupation = Filmmaker years_active =\n| 1974-present\n}}\n\n'Ricardo Costa' (born 25 January 1940 in Peniche) is a Portuguese film\ndirector and producer. [http://www.cinemaportugues.net/cinema/pessoa-\ns.asp?idpessoa=1744&lang=eng Ricardo Costa] at\n[http://www.cinemaportugues.net Portuguese Cinema] [http://estudo-v.blogspot.com/2011/04/ricardo-costa-\nfilmmaker.html Ricardo Costa] â article in Portuguese and Lithuanian\n([http://www.vu.lt/en Page about Portugal], Vilnius University)\n[http://cineuropa.org/newsdetail.aspx?documentID=9171&lang=en\nRicardo Costa] : A Look at Portugal at [http://cineuropa.org\nCineurope] O Cais do Olhar by JosÃ© de Matos-Cruz: 2th century\nPortuguese feature films, published by the Portuguese Cinematheque,\n1999 [http://rcfilms.dotster.com/RCen.pdf Ricardo Costa and\nthe flowing pictures], article by JosÃ© de Matos-Cruz He is the\nauthor of [http://rcfilms.com.sapo.pt/persotexts.htm essays] on cinema,\nvision and language.\n\nMost of his filmography consists of documentary films, many of them being\ncontaminated by fiction (docufiction and ethnofiction). He uses the techniques\nof direct cinema, non only as a tool for practising salvage ethnography but also\nas an instrument which helps him to compose a sober, \"musical\" and poetic\nnarrative, interesting cinephiles and suitable for common audiences.\n\nMists, his penultimate film, was selected for the [http://www.indiewire.com/art-\nicle/60th_venice_fest_announces_lineup_declaring_that_cinema_isnt_dead/ 60th\nVenice Film Fetival] (2003) and premiered in New York in 2011. It is the first\nfrom a biographic trilogy on time and human wanderings: Faraways. Derivas\n(Drifts), the second one an autobiographical comedy/docufiction due to be\nreleased in 2014, is a portrait of Lisbon drawn through the peregrinations of\ntwo unfit venerable brothers across the city.\n","linknr":213,"url":"Ricardo_Costa_(filmmaker)","recorded":1375081793,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Ricardo_Costa_(filmmaker)&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Ricardo_Costa_(filmmaker)&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/Peniche,_Portugal","/wiki/Portugal","/wiki/Filmmaker","/wiki/Peniche,_Portugal","/wiki/Portugal","/wiki/Film_director","/wiki/Film_producer","#cite_note-1","#cite_note-2","#cite_note-3","#cite_note-4","#cite_note-5","http://rcfilms.com.sapo.pt/persotexts.htm","/wiki/Film","/wiki/Visual_perception","/wiki/Language","/wiki/Documentary","/wiki/Docufiction","/wiki/Ethnofiction","/wiki/Direct_cinema","/wiki/Salvage_ethnography","/wiki/Cinephile","/wiki/Mists","http://www.indiewire.com/article/60th_venice_fest_announces_lineup_declaring_that_cinema_isnt_dead/","/wiki/Trilogy","/wiki/Faraways","/wiki/Lisbon","#Biography","#Filmography","#Feature_films","#Short_and_middle-length_films","#Other_genres","#See_also","#References","#External_links","/w/index.php?title=Ricardo_Costa_(filmmaker)&action=edit&section=1","/wiki/Lisbon","